obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (21290)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21290&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the All India Council for Technical`
  line `Education Act, 1987.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on such date^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. 28th March, 1988, vide notification No. S.O. 317 (E), dated 28th March, 1988, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary,`
  line `Part II, sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (21291)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21291&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "Commission" means the University Grants Commission established under section 4 of the`
  line `University Grants Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956);`
  line
  line `(b) "Council" means the All India Council for Technical Education established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(c) "Fund" means the Fund of the Council constituted under section 16;`
  line
  line `(d) "member" means a member of the Council and includes the Chairman and Vice-Chairman;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "regulations" means regulations made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(g) "technical education" means programmes of education, research and training in engineering`
  line `technology, architecture, town planning, management, pharmacy and applied arts and crafts and`
  line `such other programme or areas as the Central Government may, in consultation with the Council, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, declare;`
  line
  line `(h) "technical institution" means an institution, not being a University, which offers courses or`
  line `programmes of technical education, and shall include such other institutions as the Central Government`
  line `may, in consultation with the Council, by notification in the Official Gazette, declare as technical`
  line institutions;
  line
  line `(i) "University" means a University defined under clause (f) of section 2 of the University Grants`
  line `Commission Act, 1956 (3 of 1956) and includes an institution deemed to be a University under`
  line `section 3 of that Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (21292)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21292&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be established a Council by the name of the All India`
  line `Council for Technical Education.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power to contract and shall by the said name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The head office of the Council shall be at Delhi and the Council may, with the previous approval of`
  line `the Central Government, establish offices at other places in India.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council shall consist of the following members, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) a Vice-Chairman to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(c) the Secretary to the Government of India in the Ministry of the Central Government dealing with`
  line `education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Educational Adviser (General) to the Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Chairmen of the four Regional Committees, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f) the Chairmen of,--`
  line
  line `(i) the All India Board of Vocational Education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(ii) the All India Board of Technician Education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iii) the All India Board of Under-graduate Studies in Engineering and Technology, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(iv) the All India Board of Post-graduate Education and Research in Engineering and`
  line `Technology, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(v) the All India Board of Management Studies, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(g) one member to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the Ministry of Finance of`
  line `the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(h) one member to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the Ministry of Science and`
  line `Technology of the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(i) four members to be appointed by the Central Government by rotation to represent the Ministries`
  line `and the Departments of the Central Government, other than those specified in clauses (g) and (h);`
  line
  line `(j) two members of Parliament of whom one shall be elected by the House of the People and one by`
  line `the Council of States;`
  line
  line `(k) eight members to be appointed by the Central Government by rotation in the alphabetical order to`
  line `represent the States and the Union territories:`
  line
  line `Provided that an appointment under this clause shall be made on the recommendation of the`
  line `Government of the State, or as the case may be, the Union territory concerned;`
  line
  line `(l) four members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the organisations in the`
  line `field of industry and commerce;`
  line
  line `(m) seven members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent,--`
  line
  line `(i) the Central Advisory Board of Education;`
  line
  line `(ii) the Association of Indian Universities;`
  line
  line `(iii) the Indian Society for Technical Education;`
  line
  line `(iv) the Council of the Indian Institutes of Technology;`
  line
  line `(v) the Pharmacy Council of India;`
  line
  line `(vi) the Council of Architecture;`
  line
  line `(vii) the National Productivity Council;`
  line
  line `(n) four members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent the professional bodies in`
  line `the field of technical and management education;`
  line
  line `(o) not more than two members to be appointed by the Central Government to represent such`
  line `interests not covered by the foregoing clauses as the Central Government may deem fit;`
  line
  line `(p) the Chairman, University Grants Commission, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(q) the Director, Institute of Applied Manpower Research, New Delhi, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(r) the Director-General, Indian Council of Agricultural Research, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(s) the Director-General, Council of Scientific and Industrial Research, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(t) Member-Secretary to be appointed by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(5) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (4),--`
  line
  line `(a) the first Chairman shall be the Minister of Human Resource Development of the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(b) the first Vice-Chairman of the Council shall be the Minister of State for Education of the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(c) the first Member-Secretary of the Council shall be the Educational Adviser (Technical) of the`
  line `Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (21293)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Term of office of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21293&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The term of office of a member, other than an ex officio member, on`
  line `the first constitution of the Council shall be five years and thereafter three years.`
  line
  line `(2) If a casual vacancy occurs in the office of the Chairman, whether by reason of his death, resignation`
  line `or inability to discharge his functions owing to illness or other incapacity, the Vice-Chairman holding office`
  line `as such for the time being shall act as the Chairman and shall, unless any other person is appointed earlier as`
  line `the Chairman, hold office of the Chairman for the remainder of the term of office of the person in whose`
  line `place he is to so act.`
  line
  line `(3) If a casual vacancy occurs in the office of the Vice-Chairman or any other member, whether by reason`
  line `of his death, resignation or inability to discharge his functions owing to illness or other incapacity, such`
  line `vacancy shall be filled by the Central Government by making a fresh appointment and the member so`
  line `appointed shall hold office for the remainder of the term of office of the person in whose place he is so`
  line appointed.
  line
  line `(4) The Vice-Chairman shall perform such functions as may be assigned to him by the Chairman from`
  line `time to time.`
  line
  line `(5) The procedure to be followed by the members in the discharge of their functions shall be such as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (21294)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Meetings of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21294&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall meet at such time and places, and shall observe such`
  line `rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at`
  line `such meetings) as may be provided by regulations:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Council shall meet at least once every year.`
  line
  line `(2) The Chairman and in his absence the Vice-Chairman shall preside at the meetings of the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) If for any reason the Chairman or the Vice-Chairman is unable to attend any meeting of the Council,`
  line `any other member chosen by the members present at the meeting shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(4) All questions which come up before any meeting of the Council shall be decided by a majority of the`
  line `votes of the members present and voting, and in the event of an equality of votes, the Chairman, or in his`
  line `absence, the person presiding, shall have and exercise a second or casting vote.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (21295)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Vacancies, etc., not to invalidate proceedings of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21295&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the Council`
  line `shall be invalid merely by reason of--`
  line
  line `(a) any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Council; or`
  line
  line `(b) any defect in the appointment of a person acting as a member of the Council; or`
  line
  line `(c) any irregularity in the procedure of the Council not affecting the merits of the case.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (21296)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Temporary association of persons with the Council for particular purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21296&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council`
  line `may associate with itself, in such manner and for such purposes as may be determined by regulations, any`
  line `person whose assistance or advice it may desire in carrying out any of the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A person associated with it by the Council under sub-section (1) for any purpose shall have a right to`
  line `take part in the discussions relevant to that purpose, but shall not have a right to vote at a meeting of the`
  line `Council, and shall not be a member for any other purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (21297)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Appointment of officers and other employees of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21297&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of enabling it`
  line `efficiently to discharge its functions under this Act, the Council shall, subject to such regulations as may be`
  line `made in this behalf, appoint (whether on deputation or otherwise) such number of officers`
  line `and other employees as it may consider necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appointment of such category of officers, as may be specified in such regulations, shall`
  line `be subject to the approval of the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Every officer or other employee appointed by the Council shall be subject to such conditions of`
  line `service and shall be entitled to such remuneration as may be determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (21298)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Authentication of orders and other instruments of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21298&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions of the`
  line `Council shall be authenticated by the signature of the Chairman or any other member authorised by the`
  line `Council in this behalf, and all other instruments issued by the Council shall be authenticated by the signature`
  line `of the Member-Secretary or any other officer of the Council authorised in like manner in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (21299)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Functions of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21299&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `It shall be the duty of the Council to take all such steps as it may think`
  line `fit for ensuring coordinated and integrated development of technical education and maintenance of standards`
  line `and for the purposes of performing its functions under this Act, the Council may--`
  line
  line `(a) undertake survey in the various fields of technical education, collect data on all related matters`
  line `and make forecast of the needed growth and development in technical education;`
  line
  line `(b) coordinate the development of technical education in the country at all levels;`
  line
  line `(c) allocate and disburse out of the Fund of the Council such grants on such terms and conditions as it`
  line `may think fit to--`
  line
  line `(i) technical institutions, and`
  line
  line `(ii) Universities imparting technical education in coordination with the Commission;`
  line
  line `(d) promote innovations research and development in established and new technologies, generation,`
  line `adoption and adaptation of new technologies to meet developmental requirements and for overall`
  line `improvement of educational processes;`
  line
  line `(e) formulate schemes for promoting technical education for women, handicapped and weaker`
  line `sections of the society;`
  line
  line `(f) promote an effective link between technical education system and other relevant systems`
  line `including research and development organisations, industry and the community;`
  line
  line `(g) evolve suitable performance appraisal systems for technical institutions and Universities`
  line `imparting technical education, incorporating norms and mechanisms for enforcing accountability;`
  line
  line `(h) formulate schemes for the initial and in-service training of teachers and identify institutions or`
  line `centres and set up new centres for offering staff development programmes including continuing education`
  line `of teachers;`
  line
  line `(i) lay down norms and standards for courses, curricula, physical and instructional facilities, staff`
  line `pattern, staff qualifications, quality instructions, assessment and examinations;`
  line
  line `(j) fix norms and guidelines for charging tuition and other fees;`
  line
  line `(k) grant approval for starting new technical institutions and for introduction of new courses or`
  line `programmes in consultation with the agencies concerned;`
  line
  line `(l) advise the Central Government in respect of grant of charter to any professional body or institution`
  line `in the field of technical education conferring powers, rights and privileges on it for the promotion of such`
  line `profession in its field including conduct of examinations and awarding of membership certificates;`
  line
  line `(m) lay down norms for granting autonomy to technical institutions;`
  line
  line `(n) take all necessary steps to prevent commercialisation of technical education;`
  line
  line `(o) provide guidelines for admission of students to technical institutions and Universities imparting`
  line `technical education;`
  line
  line `(p) inspect or cause to inspect any technical institution;`
  line
  line `(q) withhold or discontinue grants in respect of courses, programmes to such technical institutions`
  line `which fail to comply with the directions given by the Council within the stipulated period of time and`
  line `take such other steps as may be necessary for ensuring compliance of the directions of the Council;`
  line
  line `(r) take steps to strengthen the existing organisations, and to set up new organisations to ensure`
  line `effective discharge of the Councils responsibilities and to create positions of professional, technical and`
  line `supporting staff based on requirements;`
  line
  line `(s) declare technical institutions at various levels and types offering courses in technical education fit`
  line `to receive grants;`
  line
  line `(t) advise the Commission for declaring any institution imparting technical education as a deemed`
  line University;
  line
  line `(u) set up a National Board of Accreditation to periodically conduct evaluation of technical`
  line `institutions or programmes on the basis of guidelines, norms and standards specified by it and to make`
  line `recommendation to it, or to the Council, or to the Commission or to other bodies, regarding recognition`
  line `or de-recognition of the institution or the programme;`
  line
  line `(v) perform such other functions as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (21300)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title Inspection.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21300&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purposes of ascertaining the financial needs of technical institution or a`
  line `University or its standards of teaching, examination and research, the Council may cause an inspection of any`
  line `department or departments of such technical institution or University to be made in such manner as may be`
  line `prescribed and by such person or persons as it may direct.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall communicate to the technical institution or University the date on which any`
  line `inspection under sub-section (1) is to be made and the technical institution or University shall be entitled to`
  line `be associated with the inspection in such manner as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council shall communicate to the technical institution or the University, its views in regard to the`
  line `results of any such inspection and may, after ascertaining the opinion of that technical institution or`
  line `University, recommend to that institution or University the action to be taken as a result of such inspection.`
  line
  line `(4) All communications to a technical institution or University under this section shall be made to the`
  line `executive authority thereof and the executive authority of the technical institution or University shall report to`
  line `the Council the action, if any, which is proposed to be taken for the purposes of implementing any such`
  line `recommendation as is referred to in sub-section (3).`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (21301)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Executive Committee of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21301&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall constitute a Committee, called the`
  line `Executive Committee for discharging such functions as may be assigned to it by the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) The Executive Committee shall consist of the following members, namely.--`
  line
  line `(a) the Chairman of the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) the Vice-Chairman of the Council;`
  line
  line `(c) Secretary to the Government of India in the Ministry of the Central Government dealing with`
  line `Education, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) two Chairmen of the Regional Committees;`
  line
  line `(e) three Chairmen of the Boards of Studies;`
  line
  line `(f) a member of the Council representing the Ministry of Finance of the Central Government, ex`
  line officio;
  line
  line `(g) four out of eight members of the Council representing the States and Union territories under`
  line `clause (k) of sub-section (4) of section 3;`
  line
  line `(h) four members with expertise and distinction in areas relevant to Technical Education to be`
  line `nominated by the Chairman of the Council;`
  line
  line `(i) the Chairman of the University Grants Commission, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(j) the Director, Institute of Applied Manpower Research, New Delhi, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(k) the Director General, Indian Council of Agricultural Research, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(l) the Member-Secretary of the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) The Chairman and the Member-Secretary of the Council shall, respectively, function as the Chairman`
  line `and the Member-Secretary of the Executive Committee.`
  line
  line `(4) The Chairman or in his absence, the Vice-Chairman of the Council shall preside at the meetings of the`
  line `Executive Committee and in the absence of both the Chairman and the Vice-Chairman, any other member`
  line `chosen by the members present at the meeting shall preside at the meeting.`
  line
  line `(5) The Executive Committee shall meet at such time and places, and shall observe such rules of`
  line `procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings (including the quorum at such meetings) as`
  line `the Council may provide by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (21302)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Boards of Studies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21302&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall establish the following Boards of Studies, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) All India Board of Vocational Education;`
  line
  line `(ii) All India Board of Technician Education;`
  line
  line `(iii) All India Board of Under-graduate Studies in Engineering and Technology;`
  line
  line `(iv) All India Board of Post-graduate Education and Research in Engineering and Technology;`
  line
  line `(v) All India Board of Management Studies.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may, if it considers necessary, establish such other Boards of Studies as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(3) Every Board of Studies shall advise the Executive Committee on academic matters falling in its area`
  line `of concern including norms, standards, model curricula, model facilities and structure of courses.`
  line
  line `(4) The area of concern, powers, the constitution and functions of the Boards of Studies shall be such as`
  line `the Council may provide by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (21303)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Regional Committees.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21303&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall establish the following Regional Committees,`
  line `namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) The Northern Regional Committee with its office at Kanpur;`
  line
  line `(ii) The Southern Regional Committee with its office at Madras;`
  line
  line `(iii) The Western Regional Committee with its office at Bombay;`
  line
  line `(iv) The Eastern Regional Committee with its office at Calcutta.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council may, if it considers necessary, establish such other Regional Committees as it may think`
  line fit.
  line
  line `(3) The Regional Committee shall advise and assist the Council to look into all aspects of planning,`
  line `promoting and regulating technical education within the region.`
  line
  line `(4) The region for which the Regional Committees may be established and the constitution and functions`
  line `of such Committees shall be prescribed by regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (21304)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Payment to the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21304&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made by Parliament`
  line `by law in this behalf, pay to the Council in each financial year such sums as may be considered necessary for`
  line `the performance of functions of the Council under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (21305)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Fund of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21305&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall have its own Fund; and all sums which may, from time`
  line `to time, be paid to it by the Central Government and all the receipts of the Council (including any sum which`
  line `any State Government or any other authority or person may hand over to the Council) shall be credited to the`
  line `Fund and all payments by the Council shall be made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) All moneys belonging to the Fund shall be deposited in such banks or invested in such manner as`
  line `may, subject to the approval of the Central Government, be decided by the Council.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council may spend such sums as it thinks fit for performing its functions under this Act, and such`
  line `sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the Fund of the Council.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (21306)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21306&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `The Council shall prepare, in such form and at such time each year as may be prescribed, a`
  line `budget in respect of the financial year next ensuing showing the estimated receipts and expenditure, and`
  line `copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (21307)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21307&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Council shall prepare once every year in such form and at such time as may be`
  line `prescribed, an annual report giving a true and full account of its activities during the previous year and copies`
  line `thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid`
  line `before both Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (21308)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21308&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall cause to be maintained such books of account`
  line `and other books in relation to its accounts in such form and in such manner as may, in consultation with the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall, as soon as may be, after closing its annual accounts prepare a statement of`
  line `accounts in such form, and forward the same to the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India by such date,`
  line `as the Central Government may, in consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General, determine.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts of the Council shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India at such`
  line `times and in such manner as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The accounts of the Council as certified by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India or`
  line `any other person appointed by him in this behalf together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `annually to the Central Government and that Government shall cause the same to be laid before both Houses`
  line `of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (21309)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Directions by the Central Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21309&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council shall, in the discharge of its functions`
  line `and duties under this Act, be bound by such directions on questions of policy as the Central Government may`
  line `give in writing to it from time to time.`
  line
  line `(2) The decision of the Central Government as to whether a question is one of policy or not shall be final.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (21310)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Power to supersede the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21310&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `(1) If the Central Government is of the opinion that the Council`
  line `is unable to perform, or has persistently made default in the performance of, the duty imposed on it by or`
  line `under this Act or has exceeded or abused its powers, or has wilfully or without sufficient cause, failed to`
  line `comply with any direction issued by the Central Government under section 20, the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, supersede the Council for such period as may be specified in the`
  line `notification:`
  line
  line `Provided that before issuing a notification under this sub-section, the Central Government shall give a`
  line `reasonable time to the Council to show cause why it should not be superseded and shall consider the`
  line `explanation and objections, if any, of the Council.`
  line
  line `(2) Upon the publication of a notification under sub-section (1) superseding the Council,--`
  line
  line `(a) all the members of the Council shall, notwithstanding that their term of office had not expired, as`
  line `from the date of supersession, vacate their offices as such members;`
  line
  line `(b) all the powers and duties which may, by or under the provisions of this Act, be exercised or`
  line `performed by or on behalf of the Council shall, during the period of supersession, be exercised and`
  line `performed by such person or persons as the Central Government may direct;`
  line
  line `(c) all property vested in the Council shall, during the period of supersession, vest in the Central`
  line Government.
  line
  line `(3) On the expiration of the period of supersession specified in the notification issued under`
  line `sub-section (1), the Central Government may--`
  line
  line `(a) extend the period of supersession for such further period as it may consider necessary; or`
  line
  line `(b) reconstitute the Council in the manner provided in section 3.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (21311)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21311&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may provide`
  line `for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the procedure to be followed by the members in the discharge of their functions;`
  line
  line `(b) the inspection of technical institutions and Universities;`
  line
  line `(c) the form and manner in which the budget and reports are to be prepared by the Council;`
  line
  line `(d) the manner in which the accounts of the Council are to be maintained; and`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which has to be, or may be, prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (21312)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21312&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Council may, by notification in the Official Gazette, make`
  line `regulations not inconsistent with the provisions of this Act, and the rules generally to carry out the purposes`
  line `of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such regulations may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the meetings of the Council and the procedure for conducting business thereat;`
  line
  line `(b) the terms and conditions of service of the officers and employees of the Council;`
  line
  line `(c) regulating the meetings of the Executive Committee and the procedure for conducting business`
  line thereat;
  line
  line `(d) the area of concern, the constitution, and powers and functions of the Board of Studies;`
  line
  line `(e) the region for which the Regional Committee be established and the constitution and functions of`
  line `such Committee.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (21313)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Rules and regulations to be laid before Parliament.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21313&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `Every rule and every regulation made under`
  line `this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in`
  line `session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive`
  line `sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions`
  line `aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or regulation or both Houses agree that`
  line `the rule or regulation should not be made, the rule or regulation shall thereafter have effect only in such`
  line `modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule or regulation.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (21314)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Power to remove difficulties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237&sectionId=21314&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_9_30_00029_198752_1517807327237
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any difficulty arises in giving effect to the provisions of the`
  line `Act, the Central Government may, by order, published in the Official Gazette, make such provisions not`
  line `inconsistent with the provisions of this Act as may appear to be necessary for removing the difficulty:`
  line
  line `Provided that no order shall be made under this section after the expiry of two years from the`
  line `commencement of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) Every order made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
